        "text_LHGLnM": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Pregnancy triggers many changes in a woman’s body, including weight gain that alters her center of gravity. This shift causes a new weight-bearing stance and increases pressure on the knees and feet.<br/><br/>Two common foot problems during pregnancy are overpronation and edema, which can lead to pain in the heel, arch, or ball of the foot.</p>",
            "text_font": "body",
            "text_size": "subtext-md",
            "text_max_size": 32,
            "text_line_height": 1.6,
